        <section>
        <h2>Downloads of CoD Mobile
        </h2>
        <p>Scince the game realesedin october 2019,CoD mobile has surpassed <b>100M+ downloads</b> on Google Play Store 
        and <b>50M+ downloads</b> on ios platform.<br>CoD mobile had shaky launch in oct 2019, but  despite of its initial problem it
         found itself at top of the Android and ios charts. CoD mobile has passed<br> 
        over <b>250M+ downloads</b> from all over all downloading platforms according to data website <mark>Sensor Tower.</mark>
         </p>
        </section>

             Revenue of CoD mobile

        <h2>Downloads of Apex Legends </h2>

        <h3>70 Million Downloads</h3>

        <p>Despite the growth in players slowing down in the months after the game's initial release, Apex Legends still boasted 70 million registered users in October 2019.</p>
    </section>
    <div>
        <h2>Active players on Apex Legends Daily</h2>

        <p>Player counter revealed the currently Playing gamers as of writing this article, which is around <b>970,533 players</b> online<br>
        so we can safely assume that around a million users on apex legends play the game daily.</p>
    </div>



<!--Revenue of Apex-->


        <section>
        <h2>Revenue of Apex Legends</h2>

        <p>Management is sticking with its previous outlook that Apex Legends and The Sims 4 will bring in between <b>$300 million
        to $400 million</b> for fiscal 2020<br> (which ends in March). While that's less than 10% of EA's annual revenue
        , management made it clear that this is just the beginning of what could be a 10-year franchise<br>
        <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/2020/02/03/electronic-arts-has-big-plans-for-apex-legends.aspx" target="_blank">more</a></p>   
    </section>
